            <title><![CDATA[Welcome to the Xtra Computing Blog]]></title>
            <link>https://www.xtra.science/blog/2026/03/01/welcome</link>
            <guid>https://www.xtra.science/blog/2026/03/01/welcome</guid>
            <pubDate>Sun, 01 Mar 2026 00:00:00 GMT</pubDate>
            <description><![CDATA[Welcome to the official blog of Xtra Computing Group at the National University of Singapore.]]></description>
            <content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>Welcome to the official blog of <strong>Xtra Computing Group</strong> at the National University of Singapore.</p>
<p>This is a space for lab members, collaborators, and friends to share research ideas, technical write-ups, project updates, and anything else that might be useful to the systems and ML community.</p>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="what-we-work-on">What We Work On<a href="https://www.xtra.science/blog/2026/03/01/welcome#what-we-work-on" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to What We Work On" title="Direct link to What We Work On" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<p>Xtra Computing Group sits at the intersection of <strong>data management systems</strong>, <strong>parallel computing</strong>, and <strong>machine learning</strong>. We build things that are fast, scalable, and principled — from GPU-accelerated ML libraries to federated learning benchmarks to LLM privacy toolkits.</p>
<p>A few highlights from recent work:</p>
<ul>
<li class=""><strong><a href="https://github.com/Xtra-Computing/LLM-PBE" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="">LLM-PBE</a></strong> (SIGMOD 2024, Best Paper Nomination) — a toolkit for evaluating data privacy risks in large language models.</li>
<li class=""><strong><a href="https://github.com/Xtra-Computing/VertiBench" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="">VertiBench</a></strong> (ICLR 2024) — advancing feature distribution diversity in vertical federated learning benchmarks.</li>
<li class=""><strong><a href="https://github.com/Xtra-Computing/ModelGo" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="">Model Go</a></strong> (WWW 2024, Oral) — a practical tool for machine learning license analysis.</li>
<li class=""><strong><a href="https://github.com/Xtra-Computing/thundergbm" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="">ThunderGBM</a></strong> / <strong><a href="https://github.com/Xtra-Computing/thundersvm" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="">ThunderSVM</a></strong> — GPU-accelerated gradient boosting and SVM libraries with thousands of users.</li>
</ul>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="who-can-write-here">Who Can Write Here<a href="https://www.xtra.science/blog/2026/03/01/welcome#who-can-write-here" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Who Can Write Here" title="Direct link to Who Can Write Here" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<p>Everyone. Lab members, visiting researchers, collaborators, and anyone in the community with something interesting to say. If you have a research insight, a systems trick, a paper walkthrough, or a tutorial — this blog is for you.</p>
<p>See <a href="https://github.com/Xtra-Computing/blog/blob/main/CONTRIBUTING.md" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="">CONTRIBUTING.md</a> for how to submit a post via pull request.</p>
<h2 class="anchor anchorTargetStickyNavbar_Vzrq" id="links">Links<a href="https://www.xtra.science/blog/2026/03/01/welcome#links" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Links" title="Direct link to Links" translate="no">​</a></h2>
<ul>
<li class="">Lab website: <a href="https://www.xtra.science/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="">www.xtra.science</a></li>
<li class="">GitHub: <a href="https://github.com/Xtra-Computing" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="">github.com/Xtra-Computing</a></li>
<li class="">HuggingFace: <a href="https://huggingface.co/Xtra-Computing" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="">huggingface.co/Xtra-Computing</a></li>
</ul>]]></content:encoded>
